# Rule 1 — Write-access allowlist

Cursor in agent mode may create / edit / delete files **only inside** the directories listed in `.figma-pipeline/config.json` → `writeScope.allowedDirs`. Everything else in the project is read-only.

## Before `/init` runs (bootstrap)

Until `.figma-pipeline/config.json` exists, only these roots are writable:

- `.figma-pipeline/**`
- `.mcp.json`
- `.codex/**`
- `/tmp/**`

## After `/init`

The wizard composes `writeScope.allowedDirs` from the configured paths (token output, component dirs, icon output, story / test output when not co-located). Plus always: `.figma-pipeline/**`, `.mcp.json`, `.codex/**`, `/tmp/**`.

## Always-blocked

Regardless of the allowlist:

- `node_modules/**`, `dist/**`, `build/**`, `.next/**`, `.turbo/**`, `coverage/**`
- `package-lock.json`, `yarn.lock`, `pnpm-lock.yaml`
- `.env`, `.env.*` (except `.env.example` — see `env-access.mdc`)
- `tailwind.config.{js,ts,cjs,mjs}` when `cssSystem.name == "tailwind-v4"` (v4 is CSS-only)

## Escape

The escape hatch `FP_ALLOW_RESTRICTED_WRITE=1` (legacy `HK_ALLOW_RESTRICTED_WRITE=1` still accepted) lives in the shell env, which Cursor cannot read. The user must explicitly tell Cursor to override; otherwise refuse the write and report.

## If you find yourself wanting to write outside the allowlist

Stop. Either (a) ask the user to extend `config.writeScope.allowedDirs` and re-validate, or (b) ask the user to override explicitly. Do not silently bypass.
